enhanced_by.reason: The creation of the LineFloat object is necessary to have a valid instance to test for intersection with a Rectangle.
The minimum bounding rectangle (MBR) of the LineFloat object can be used to pre-check if there is any possibility of intersection with the given Rectangle.
Both methods check for intersection with geometric shapes, which can inform the construction of assertions for the intersects(Rectangle) method.
The intersects(Point) method checks for intersection with a Point, which can be similar in logic to checking for intersection with a Rectangle.
The intersects(Circle) method checks for intersection with a Circle, which can provide insights into how to construct assertions for the intersects(Rectangle) method.
